transcript: My parents’ dog is ugly. There’s no other word for it. This isn’t “pug-ugly.” It’s just straight up ugly. He looks like a goblin. But god damn, I love that dog. He has no clue that he looks like something from Jim Henson’s Creature Shop, and has the most awful breath you could imagine. I turned him into a character with his own voice, to make him even more like a goblin. He’s got a whole back story about how he sneaks out of the house at night to eat corpses, which his how he got his breath. His favorite cereal is Corpse Crunch, as a matter of fact, and he loves to make puns about death. It’s a mismatch with his being a really sweet dog, but I prefer making him talk about grave matters, of corpse.
